PDRC-153#1 Warning
Gated clock check  
Net s7mmcm1_clkin is a gated clock net sourced by a combinational pin s7mmcm1_clkin_inst/O, cell s7mmcm1_clkin_inst. This is not good design practice and will likely impact performance. For SLICE registers, for example, use the CE pin to control the loading of data.
Related violations: <none>

PLHOLDVIO-2#1 Warning
Non-Optimal connections which could lead to hold violations  
A LUT s7mmcm1_clkin_inst is driving clock pin of 8 cells. This could lead to large hold time violations. Involved cells are:
FDCE_10, FDCE_11, FDCE_12, FDCE_13, FDCE_14, FDCE_15, FDCE_8, FDCE_9
Related violations: <none>

REQP-1839#1 Warning
RAMB36 async control check  
The RAMB36E1 storage_10_reg_0 has an input control pin storage_10_reg_0/RSTREGB (net: sys_rst) which is driven by a register (FDPE_1) that has an active asychronous set or reset. This may cause corruption of the memory contents and/or read values when the set/reset is asserted and is not analyzed by the default static timing analysis. It is suggested to eliminate the use of a set/reset to registers driving this RAMB pin or else use a synchronous reset in which the assertion of the reset is timed by default.
